## Session Protocol
1. Run `npx tsc --noEmit` — document error count
2. Check /system_health.md — current status
3. Check /AGENT_BOARD.md — what's in flight
4. Check open PRs — review, merge, or rebase
5. Work on highest priority from stack
6. Run `npx tsc --noEmit` again — must be 0
7. Update /system_health.md and /AGENT_BOARD.md
8. Commit with descriptive message

## Merge Order (always this sequence)
1. Security patches (Agent 08)
2. TypeScript/build fixes (Agent 05)
3. Infrastructure — DB migrations, edge functions (Agent 04/05)
4. Core feature fixes — generate flow above all (Agent 04)
5. New features (Agent 04)
6. Polish, copy, design fixes (Agent 03/11)

## Conflict Resolution
When agents conflict on the same file:
1. Security fixes win over everything
2. Bug fixes win over features
3. Design fixes win over copy changes
4. Lower-numbered agent yields to higher-priority domain

## Priority Stack (current)
- P0: Generate flow integrity — DONE
- P1: Kill Amadeus — DONE
- P2: CI pipeline — DONE
- P3: Analytics instrumentation (PostHog) — Agent 10 leads, Agent 04 implements
- P4: Rate limiting on edge functions — Agent 08 leads
- P5: Booking.com real AID — BLOCKED (Quinn manual action)

## NEVER
- Merge a PR with TypeScript errors
- Hardcode hex colors, non-Lucide icons, or emojis
- Put API keys in client code
- Skip the session protocol
- Leave system_health.md stale

## ALWAYS
- Run tsc at start and end of every session
- Update AGENT_BOARD.md when assigning or completing work
- Write to system_health.md after significant changes
- Small focused PRs (one concern, max 10 files, rebased on main)
- Verify generate flow still works after any change

## Definition of Done
A task is done when:
- Code is on main branch
- npx tsc --noEmit returns 0
- system_health.md updated
- No new lint errors introduced
- AGENT_BOARD.md reflects completion
